title.narrative: Emergency Water and Electricity Services Upgrading Project

description.narrative: The objective of the Project is to: (a) restore and increase the access of the population of the Recipient's capital city of Bissau to safe water and improve the quality of water services; (b) improve the reliability of electricity supply to the population of Bissau; and (c) improve the performance of EAGB.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2 Section V.2 | Description: No later than three months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shallappoint and thereafter maintain, at all times during Project implementation, the board of directors of EAGB, with terms ofreference and composition satisfactory to the Association | Due Date: 30-Dec-2017

Finance Agreement: 1. Mandate and staffing of the PIU | Description: The Recipient shall modify the mandate of the ProjectImplementation Unit no later than one month after the Effective Date and thereafter maintain at all times during the implementationof the Project, a Project Implementation Unit within the administrative structure of MERI, with terms of reference and resourcessatisfactory to the Association and supported by qualified and experienced personnel. | Due Date: 30-Sep-2014

Finance Agreement: 2. Partnership Agreement with EAGB | Description: To facilitate the carrying out of Components 1.2, 2.1 and 3.3of the Project, the Recipient through MEPRI shall, no later than one month after the Effective Date, enter into (and thereaftermaintain) a partnership agreement with EAGB, under terms and conditions approved by the Association. | Due Date: 30-Sep-2014

Finance Agreement: 3. Preparation of Safeguards Documents | Description: On or before three months after the Effective Date, theProject Implementing Unit shall adopt in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, and shall furnish to the Association,the Environmental and Social Management Framework and the Resettlement Policy Framework. | Due Date: 30-Nov-2014

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.A.1 (a) | Description: The Recipient shall modify the mandate of the Project ImplementationUnit no later than one month after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain at all times during the implementation of theProject, a Project implementation unit within the administrative structure of MEF, with terms of reference and resourcessatisfactory to the Association, and supported by qualified and experienced personnel | Due Date: 30-Oct-2017

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.A.3 (a) | Description: The Recipient shall establish, not later than two months after theEffective Date and thereafter maintain at all times during Project implementation, a Project Steering Committee with a mandate,composition and resources satisfactory to the Association (Project Steering Committee). | Due Date: 30-Nov-2017

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.C.1 (c) | Description: EAGB shall: (i) no later than nine (9) months after the EffectiveDate, establish, and thereafter maintain throughout Project implementation, a financial management system and prepare financialstatements in accordance with consistently applied accounting standards acceptable to the Association; (ii) have said financialstatements audited by independent auditors for each fiscal year of EAGB | Due Date: 30-Jun-2018

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.D.1 | Description: No later than four months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shallapprove, and shall cause EAGB to adopt and thereafter maintain throughout Project implementation, a Management Improvement Plan |Due Date: 30-Jan-2018

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.D.2 | Description: No later than six months after the Recipient’s approval of theManagement Improvement Plan, the Recipient shall: (a) with support of the Project Implementation Unit execute a Services Contractwith the Services Provider in accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule 2 to this Agreement; and (b) thereaftercause the Project Implementation Unit to maintain at all times during the implementation of the project | Due Date: 30-Jul-2018

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.D.3 | Description: Within two months from the date of signing of the Services Contract, theRecipient shall cause EAGB to: (i) proceed with any corporate nominations prescribed by the applicable laws, including, anyrepresentative from the Services Provider pursuant to the Services Contract; and (ii) submit to the Association an opinion oropinions satisfactory to the Association of counsel acceptable to the Association | Due Date: 30-Sep-2018

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.D.4 | Description: The Recipient shall no later than six months after the Effective Dateenter into a Performance Contract with EAGB under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Association and thereafter maintain atall times during the implementation of the Project said Performance Contract | Due Date: 30-Mar-2018

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section I.D.5 | Description: The Recipient, with the support of the PIU, shall have a semi-annualtechnical and financial review of the implementation of Services Contract and Performance Contract carried out by the ContractAuditors and submit its report no later than two months after the end of the relevant semester to the Services Provider, theProject Steering Committee and to the Association. | Frequency: Semi-annual

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section V.1 | Description: No later than two months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shallcause EAGB to amend the company by-laws, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, to comply with OHADA Legislation |Due Date: 30-Nov-2017

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section V.3 | Description: The Recipient shall cause EAGB to adopt and thereafter implement aMaintenance, Repair and Rehabilitation Plan, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association | Frequency: Continuous

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section V.4 | Description: The Recipient shall: (a) not later than twenty-four months from theEffective Date, cause EAGB to carry out an inventory of EAGB’s assets and liabilities, and prepare and submit to the Associationfor its review and written approval the financial restructuring plan; and (b) within six months from its review by the Association,adopt the financial restructuring plan and take and, as the case may be. | Due Date: 30-Sep-2019

Finance Agreement: Schedule 2 Section V.5 | Description: No later than six months after the Effective Date, the Recipient shalladopt the Generation Plan, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date: 30-Mar-2018
